cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Requirements Engineering (RE) approaches in agile software projects.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper specifically addresses security requirements in software development.
- cs.SD (Software Development) is relevant as the paper discusses modifying agile methods and introducing new artifacts to handle security requirements.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possibility as the paper touches on the societal impact of security in software development.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on programming language features or tools used to address security requirements in agile development.
